Orientalist representations of the “Arab woman.” By attending to Arab women’s narration of desire and identity, queer Arab critique substantiates queer Arab histories while challenging Orientalist and Arab national paradigms that erase queer subjects. In this way, Shomali frames queerness and Arabness as relational and transnational subject formations and contends that prioritizing transnational collectivity over politics of authenticity, respectability, and inclusion can help lead toward queer freedom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminismzArab countries. 0aLesbianism in literature. 0aLesbianism in motion pictures. 0aLesbianismzArab countries. 0aQueer theory. 0aSexzArab countries. 0aWomenxSocial conditionszArab countries. 0aWomenzArab countriesxSocial conditions. 0aWomen, ArabxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023906?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023906423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023906/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles